data.description: Rare Opportunity for 2900sqft, bright, open, all brick, pool home in the high-demand golf course community of Tiger Point. There are Hurricane shutters for additional protection from storms. X-Flood zone= high and dry in Tiger Point (also a fairly rare find). There is floor to ceiling windows on both exterior walls of the spacious dining/living room that makes your feel that you are one with the natural beauty that is Tiger Point. This living room is so bright with natural light you won't need to turn on a light in the daytime. The west side windows all have custom easy roll shades or plantation shutters. The spacious 31x23' living room is wide open for whatever you can dream of with an electric fireplace in the middle for ambience. The large kitchen is eloquently and intelligently designed and is perfect for gathering with friends. With the pool with new pool equipment just outside the back doors, this large home is perfect for entertaining, hosting parties, or gathering with family & neighbors. This home is a 3 bedroom 3 full bath with an additional a large 31'x16' loft area over the living room that makes a perfect office or could be easily made into an additional bedroom. One of the additional bedrooms has an updated bathroom in it and can double as a second primary suite. The primary bedroom is spacious and has a sliding glass door to poolside. There are 2 walk-in closets between the primary bedroom and bathroom. The Japanese spa themed primary bathroom will have you easily unwinding and relaxing will offering plenty of eloquent storage in custom-made wood cabinetry. You will love the large back yard with the salt water pool with recently updated pool equipment and still plenty of room to play. Just 700 yards from Soundside Park & Beach where the kids and dogs can run, play, fish, and swim in the Sound. Also just 500 yards from Tiki-at-the-Turn. You must see to appreciate this beautiful one-of-a-kind home!
